The fountain survived well past the bandstand, we have Town Commissioners minutes on site as well and

&quot;4th July 1887 - Mr Flemings’ design for a new fountain on the promenade costing £7-18-6 was accepted&quot; 

The fountain survived intact until around the 1950's sometime then it was removed. Local rumour has it some part of it survives, but as yet we have been unable to find any trace of it.
